"{\"uid\": \"goodereader.com-blog-electronic-readers-parisian-booksellers-win-olympic-standoff\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"With the Paris Olympics just days away, there is heartening news for the Seine River Booksellers.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 99, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 5, \"to\": 23}, {\"ngram\": \"news\", \"from\": 60, \"to\": 64}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River Booksellers\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 96}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As reported inApril 2023, these iconic kiosks faced mounting pressure to dismantle ahead of the Olympic Games' opening ceremony, set to unfold not in a stadium but along the river.\", \"from\": 101, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"inApril\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"these iconic kiosks\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 146}, {\"ngram\": \"mounting pressure\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 170}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games' opening ceremony\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 228}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 271, \"to\": 280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers envisioned a spectacle where athletes would parade down the Seine in various watercrafts, transforming the river into a dynamic global stage.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5833728712804252e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 292}, {\"ngram\": \"a spectacle\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 315}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 330}, {\"ngram\": \"various watercrafts\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"a dynamic global stage\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The primary concern cited by authorities was security.\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 490, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The primary concern\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 489}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They expressed doubts about thoroughly searching the diverse array of books and artifacts within the kiosks for potential threats during the event.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"doubts\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"the diverse array\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"artifacts\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"the kiosks\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"potential threats\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Supporters of relocation argued that the complex marketplace could inadvertently harbor concealed harmful items or individuals.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 766, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Supporters\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"relocation\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"the complex marketplace\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 699}, {\"ngram\": \"harmful items\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 750}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 765}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, these bookstalls are more than mere marketplaces; they embody Parisian heritage.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these bookstalls\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"mere marketplaces\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisian heritage\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Originating as hubs for pamphlets and dissent during political upheavals, they have evolved into one of theworld's largest and oldest open-air book markets.Annually, approximately 300,000 books, paintings, and artworks pass through these stalls, making them a cherished cultural landmark for locals and tourists alike.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hubs\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"pamphlets\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"dissent\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"political upheavals\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"theworld's largest and oldest open-air book markets\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"approximately 300,000 books\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"paintings\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"artworks\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"these stalls\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1152}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parisian booksellers have astoried historyof resilience against authority.\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecological_resilience\", \"score\": 0.9994117723055195, \"rank\": 0.0005798425491481112, \"text\": \"resilience\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecological_resilience\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecological_resilience\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Parisian booksellers\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"authority\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1247}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Initially used for distributing anti-monarchist materials, the stalls relocated along the Seine in 1649 after a royal prohibition near Pont Neuf.\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5833728712804252e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anti-monarchist materials\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"the stalls\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"a royal prohibition\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1378}, {\"ngram\": \"Pont Neuf\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the French Revolution, looted books from aristocratic libraries often found their way to these stalls.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1504, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the French Revolution\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"aristocratic libraries\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1487}, {\"ngram\": \"these stalls\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1503}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They later played a vital role in disseminating anti-Nazi propaganda during World War II, with books serving as clandestine messengers.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a vital role\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-Nazi propaganda\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1573}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"clandestine messengers\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even under Napoleon's rule, attempts to regulate them were met with defiance as they persisted.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3262517784400345e-37, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"defiance\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite offers from the government to assist in temporary relocation, the booksellers vehemently protested.\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"offers\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"temporary relocation\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"the booksellers\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jerome Callais, head of the Paris Booksellers' Cultural Association representing 88% of sellers, emphasized toThe Local,\\\"We have no intention of moving.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1846, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerome\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2519941328430947e-14, \"text\": \"Jerome\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerome\"}, {\"begin\": 1874, \"end\": 1879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4017316566200636e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"88%\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"sellers\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"no intention\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are a major symbol of Paris, having been here for 450 years.\\\"\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4017316566200636e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a major symbol\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"450 years\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this year, French President Emmanuel Macron intervened to preserve the bouquinistes' presence.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2084, \"end\": 2100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bouquinistes' presence\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amidst calls for relocation, Macron emphasized their integral role in Paris's living heritage.\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2197, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.513443793164034e-17, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4017316566200636e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"calls\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"relocation\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2195}, {\"ngram\": \"their integral role\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His directive to protect the kiosks from displacement underscores their enduring significance in the city's cultural fabric.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His directive\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2276}, {\"ngram\": \"the kiosks\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"displacement underscores\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"their enduring significance\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2356}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's cultural fabric\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Paris readies itself for the Olympics, the decision to retain the Seine River Booksellers reflects the city's commitment to preserving its rich cultural identity.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4017316566200636e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7909340048680874e-37, \"text\": \"Seine River\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's commitment\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"its rich cultural identity\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It ensures that amidst the sporting spectacle, the spirit of Paris's literary and artistic heritage remains firmly anchored along the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2616, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc